The bash shell script "matrix" performs basic matrix computations. 

Usage:
    matrix dims [MATRIX]
    matrix transpose [MATRIX]
    matrix mean [MATRIX]
    matrix add MATRIX_LEFT MATRIX_RIGHT
    matrix multiply MATRIX_LEFT MATRIX_RIGHT

Input for matrices represent filenames. Will output to stdout. 

Description of Commands:
dims 
    prints dimensions of the matrix as the number of rows in <rows> <cols> formate
transpose
    reflects elements of matrix along main diagonal
mean
    takes MxN matrix and returns 1xN row vector
add
    adds two matrices pairwise
multiply
    multiplies two matrices
